OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,415,410,120,260,000,100
PN,41405
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F414A1777554668
OL,3,CPolice patrols increased to support
OL,4,CJewish communities across the Thames
OL,5,CValley
OL,7,F"We are really proud that the Thames
OL,8,FValley is a diverse, inclusive and
OL,9,Fvibrant place, and we stand together
OL,10,Fin solidarity with all those affected
OL,11,Fby today's news."
OL,13,FResponding to the attack, Sir Keir
OL,14,FStarmer vowed that the Government
OL,15,Fwould address the causes of
OL,16,Fantisemitism, provide more funding for
OL,17,Fsecurity at Jewish sites and tackle
OL,18,F"malign state actors" linked to recent
OL,19,Fviolence.
OL,26,@oD@AOUsD@QO]zD@AOUzD@UO]
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G5/6
